<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="192" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,417,694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,453,478]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[613,770,453,478]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ubsunurica">
<emphasis box="[613,770,453,478]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">B. ubsunurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which it can be distinguished by its lighter coloration (cf. 
<figureCitation box="[198,270,489,514]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[199,1379,195,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[199,1387,195,1870]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Male palp and habitus of Berlandina ubsunurica. 1 – 4 palp, ventral, prolateral, retrolateral and dorsal; 5 palpal tibia, dorsal; 6 – 8 bulbus, ventral, retrolateral and apical; 9 habitus. Abbreviations: Em embolus, Ma median apophysis, Tr tegular ridge, Tt tooth of RTA." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249733/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">
Figs 
<number box="[256,270,489,513]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[311,341,489,513]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 19" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1311,1334]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,193,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[161,1426,193,1291]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 19. Epigyne of Berlandina ubsunurica (10 – 12), epigyne and habitus of B. nenilini (13 – 16) and B. hui (17 – 19). 10 – 11, 13, 15, 17 epigyne, ventral; 12, 14, 18 epigyne, dorsal; 16, 19 habitus. Abbreviation: Op outgrowths of lateral pocket." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/249734/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">
<number box="[311,341,489,513]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
), longer tibial apophysis (cf. fig. 
<number box="[729,756,489,513]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" value="13.0">13</number>
D in 
<bibRefCitation author="Song" box="[818,1013,489,514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" refString="Song, D. X., Zhu, M. S. &amp; Zhang, F. (2004) Fauna Sinica: Invertebrata Vol. 39: Arachnida: Araneae: Gnaphosidae. Science Press, Beijing, 362 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="2004">
Song 
<emphasis box="[884,943,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[953,1013,489,513]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), narrow peak of epigynal fovea and closely spaced receptacles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="192" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,417,694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,561,586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Comments</emphasis>
. This species was well described by 
<bibRefCitation box="[737,941,561,586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" refString="Song, D. X., Zhu, M. S. &amp; Zhang, F. (2004) Fauna Sinica: Invertebrata Vol. 39: Arachnida: Araneae: Gnaphosidae. Science Press, Beijing, 362 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book">
Song 
<emphasis box="[801,857,561,586]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[871,933,561,585]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Here we provide figures only of the female. Male specimens are known by the description in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hu" box="[700,894,598,622]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" refString="Hu, J. L. &amp; Wu, W. G. (1989) Spiders from agricultural regions of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, China. Shandong University Publishing House, Jinan, 435 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1989">
Hu &amp; Wu (
<number box="[825,886,598,622]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In all later papers authors used figures made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hu" box="[151,345,634,658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" refString="Hu, J. L. &amp; Wu, W. G. (1989) Spiders from agricultural regions of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, China. Shandong University Publishing House, Jinan, 435 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1989">
Hu &amp; Wu (
<number box="[276,337,634,658]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
